<section id="fs-id2017809" class="free-response">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id2602425">
<problem id="fs-id2158627"><para id="fs-id2158628">Describe anaphylactic shock in someone sensitive to peanuts?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2525095"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2575326">The peanuts cause high levels of mast cell degranulation in the throats of these individuals. The histamine released increases vascular permeability, causing edema and (swelling), making breathing difficult. This must be treated with epinephrine as soon as possible.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1629815">
<problem id="fs-id1907243"><para id="fs-id1907244">Describe rheumatic fever and how tolerance is broken.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id2346449"><label/>
<para id="fs-id2146357">Antibody response to the cell walls of β-<emphasis effect="italics">Streptococcus</emphasis> cross-reacts with the heart muscle. Complement is then activated and the heart is damaged, leading to abnormal function. Tolerance is broken because heart myosin antigens are similar to antigens on the β-<emphasis effect="italics"> Streptococcus</emphasis> bacteria.</para></solution>
</exercise>
